  "prompt": "How can I delete iPhone battery usage stats?",
  "response": "To reset battery usage statistics on an iPhone, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to Settings\n\n2. Tap \"Battery\"\n\n3. Tap the clock icon next to \"Battery Percentage\"\n\n4. If you want to completely reset, you can:\n- Restart your iPhone\n- Perform a soft reset\n- Update to the latest iOS version\n\nNote: These steps will clear recent battery usage data, but won't permanently delete historical battery statistics stored by iOS.\n\nFor a more comprehensive reset, you might need to:\n- Backup your iPhone\n- Perform a factory reset\n- Restore from backup\n\nIf you're experiencing persistent battery issues, Apple Support recommends checking battery health in Settings > Battery > Battery Health.",
